==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maxillary
<hw>Max"il*la*ry</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>maxillaris</ets>, fr.
<ets>maxilla</ets> jawbone, jaw: cf. F. <ets>maxillaire</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to either the upper or
the lower jaw, but now usually applied to the upper jaw only.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The principal maxillary bone; the
maxilla.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a
maxilla.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maxilliform</ent>⟦br⟧
